main event: Witness observed a jet aircraft flying north, which exploded and the pilot parachuted down rapidly.
interesting points: The aircraft was estimated to be at 8000 feet,The sighting lasted approximately 5 seconds,The observer was about 5 miles from the aircraft,Two F-89 aircraft were later vectored to the area but were unable to observe due to darkness,The parachute was estimated to land in sections 27 or 28 of Township 34, Southrange Eleven West.
witness description: Mr. Agnesi, located approximately five miles from the aircraft
